I don’t know anything about 667’s or implementing the Mithril seeds game, but that’s a common compiler error. It means that your World class doesn’t contain the method spawnTempGroundObject. The tutorial you followed may not have been for your exact source. Check if your version of the World class has a similar, differently named method. In the future, you can use Eclipse to help you identify and fix compiler errors before they happen.
